    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to the phase in the Ubaid period in southern Mesopotamia from about 5000 to 4500 BCE. The phase is characterized by monocrhrome pottery with simple geometric designs and increased connections with areas outside of southern Mesopotamia.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Se refiere a la fase en el período Ubaid en Mesopotamia del sur de aproximadamente 5000 al 4500 a.C. La fase se caracteriza por cerámica monocromática con diseños geométricos simples y relaciones cada vez mayores con áreas fuera de Mesopotamia del sur.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Verwijst naar de fase in de Ubaid-periode in het zuiden van Mesopotamië van circa 5.000 tot 4.500 v. Chr. Deze fase kenmerkt zich door monochroom aardewerk met simpele geometrische patronen, en toenemende contacten met gebieden buiten het zuiden van Mesopotamië.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>指自西元前5000年至西元前4500年間，於美索不達米亞南部發展之烏貝德時代當中的一個時期。此時期的特色為上繪有簡單幾何設計圖案的單色陶器，以及與美索不達米亞南部以外地區逐漸增加的聯繫。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
